Vice President Biden and Valerie Jarrett met with leaders of national disabilities and veteran's advocacy groups to express support for ratification of the Disabilities Treaty. The Vice President emphasized the importance of ratifying the treaty to ensure equal opportunities for Americans with disabilities, including veterans and wounded warriors, in other countries. He believes that people with disabilities around the world should have the same access and opportunities as their fellow citizens, and that the United States should encourage other countries to meet the same high standards.